    "body": "Installing packages with a lot of dependencies does not have an easy way of judging the current progress (apart from running `spack spec -I pkg` in another terminal). This change makes Spack update the terminal's title with status information, including the current installation phase as well as information about the current and total number of packages.\r\n\r\nCurrently only tested on Fedora with GNOME Terminal (where it works :smile:).",
